e:T609,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How does Codepliant detect cookies in my code?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Codepliant scans for cookie-setting patterns: document.cookie, Set-Cookie headers, express-session, cookie-parser, next-auth session cookies, and third-party scripts that set cookies (Google Analytics, Facebook Pixel, etc.). It also detects localStorage and sessionStorage usage."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does the generated policy include cookie categories?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Codepliant categorizes detected cookies into: strictly necessary, performance, functional, and targeting/advertising. This categorization aligns with GDPR and ePrivacy Directive requirements for cookie consent."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does Codepliant generate a cookie banner?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. In addition to the cookie policy document, Codepliant can generate a cookie banner widget that you can embed in your application. The banner includes accept/reject options and links to your cookie policy."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is this compliant with GDPR and ePrivacy?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The generated cookie policy includes GDPR-required information: what cookies are used, their purpose, duration, and whether they are first-party or third-party. It also includes consent language required by the ePrivacy Directive. We recommend legal review for your specific jurisdiction."}}]}b:["$","$1","c",{"children":[[["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$e"}}],["$","script",null,{"type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"SoftwareApplication\",\"name\":\"Codepliant Cookie Policy Generator\",\"applicationCategory\":\"DeveloperApplication\",\"operatingSystem\":\"macOS, Linux, Windows\",\"description\":\"Free cookie policy generator that scans your codebase for cookies, tracking scripts, and storage patterns.\",\"offers\":{\"@type\":\"Offer\",\"price\":\"0\",\"priceCurrency\":\"USD\"}}"}}],["$","article",null,{"className":"py-20 px-6","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-[680px] mx-auto","children":[["$","p",null,{"className":"text-sm font-medium text-accent mb-4 tracking-wide uppercase","children":"Free Tool"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6","children":"Free Cookie Policy Generator for Developers"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-lg text-muted mb-12","children":"GDPR and ePrivacy require you to disclose every cookie your application sets. Codepliant scans your code for cookies, local storage, session management, and third-party tracking scripts, then generates an accurate cookie policy."}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-16","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6","children":"What Codepliant detects"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"space-y-6 text-base text-muted leading-relaxed","children":["$","p",null,{"children":"Most developers don't know every cookie their application sets. Third-party scripts, analytics SDKs, and authentication libraries all set cookies that need to be disclosed. Codepliant scans your source code and dependency tree to find them all."}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-6","children":[["$","div","document.cookie usage",{"className":"bg-surface rounded-xl px-4 py-3 text-sm","children":"document.cookie usage"}],"$Lf","$L10","$L11","$L12","$L13","$L14","$L15","$L16","$L17"]}]]}],"$L18","$L19","$L1a"]}]}]],null,"$L1b"]}]
